resourceContent

public static Action resourceContent(java.lang.String resourcePath)
Writes content and content-type of resource file to response. Tries to detect content type based on file extension. If can not detect => content-type is not set. For now there are following bindings:
  • .xml => application/xml
  • .json => application/xml

resourceContent

public static Action resourceContent(java.net.URL resourceUrl)
Does the same as Action.resourceContent(), the only difference is that it accepts an URL instead of resource path.
